  Arcane Tradition: School of Divination
    Divination Savant: Gold and Time to copy an divination spell into your spellbook is halved.
    Portent: [After Long Rest] Glimpses of the future
      Roll 2 d20s and record the numbers (each can only be used once and go away at a long rest)
      You can replace any attack roll, saving throw, or ability check made by you or a creature you can see with one of these rolls. Must be done before the roll is made.
    Expert Divination:
      When you cast divination spell of 2nd LVL or higher using a spell slot,
      regain 1 expended spell slot that is of lower LVL than the cast spell and lower than 5th LVL
    The Third Eye: [Once Per Rest: Use Action] to increase powers of perception until you take the next rest.
      Choose 1: Darkvision, Etheral Sight, Greater Comprehension, See Invisibility
    Greater Portent: 3 d20s for Portent
  Arcave Recovery: [Once Per Long Rest] Study your Spellbook.
    After finishing a Rest
    you can choose Expended Spell Slots to Recover.
    Recovered Spell Slots can have a combined level <= half your Wizard LVL (rounded up) and < 6th LVL Spell Slot

